{"apiVersion":"console.openshift.io/v1","kind":"QuickStarts","metadata":{"name":"getting-started-api-designer","annotations":{"draft":true,"order":1}},"spec":{"version":0.1,"type":{"text":"Quick start","color":"green"},"displayName":"Getting started with OpenShift API Designer","durationMinutes":10,"icon":"data:image/svg+xml;base64,","description":"<div id=\"description\" class=\"exampleblock\">\n<div class=\"content\">\n<div class=\"paragraph\">\n<p>Learn how to create your first API Designer design in OpenShift API Designer.</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>","prerequisites":["A Red Hat identity","Access to the <a href=\"https://console.redhat.com/application-services/api-designer\">Red Hat OpenShift API Designer web console</a>"],"introduction":"<div id=\"introduction\" class=\"exampleblock\">\n<div class=\"content\">\n<div class=\"paragraph\">\n<p>Welcome to the quick start for OpenShift API Designer.\nIn this quick start, you&#8217;ll learn how to &#8230;&#8203;</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>","tasks":["<div class=\"sect1\">\n<h2 id=\"proc-creating-schema-api-design_getting-started-ad\">Creating an API Designer schema or API design</h2>\n<div class=\"sectionbody\">\n<div class=\"paragraph _abstract\">\n<p>Use the OpenShift API Designer web console to create an API Designer schema or API design.</p>\n</div>\n<div class=\"olist\"><div class=\"title\">Procedure</div><div class=\"task-pflist\"><h6 data-ouia-component-type=\"PF4/Title\" data-ouia-safe=\"true\" data-ouia-component-id=\"OUIA-Generated-Title-1\" class=\"pf-c-title pf-m-md task-pflist-title\">Procedure</h6><ol type=\"1\" class=\"pf-c-list task-pflist-list task-pflist-list--proc\"><li class=\"task-pflist-list__item--proc task-pflist-list__item\"><span class=\"task-pflist-list__item__content\"><p>In the <a href=\"https://console.redhat.com/application-services/api-designer/\">API Designer web console</a>, click &#8230;&#8203;</p> </span></li><li class=\"task-pflist-list__item--proc task-pflist-list__item\"><span c